f(x)
[a,b]
|f(x)| \le M
\displaystyle \left|\int_a^b f(x)\,dx\right| \le M(b-a)
\{a=x_0,x_1,...,x_n=b\}
\int_a^b f
M(b-a)
  \sum_{i=1}^n f(x_i)(x_i-x_{i-1})
  |\sum_{i=1}^n f(x_i)(x_i-x_{i-1})|\leq \sum_{i=1}^n |f(x_i)(x_i-x_{i-1})|\leq \sum_{i=1}^n M x_i-x_{i-1}=M(b-a)
|\int_a^b f|\leq \int_a^b|f|
|f(x)|\leq M
\left|\int_a^b f(x)dx \right|\leq \int_{a}^b |f(x)|dx\leq \int_{a}^{b}Mdx=M\int_a^bdx=M(b-a),
